50|$|David Ralph Bennion was {{a leading}} California {{winemaker}} who was the founder and winemaker at <b>Ridge</b> <b>Vineyards</b> in California from 1959-1969. From an early period, Bennion labeled <b>Ridge</b> <b>Vineyards</b> wines by vineyard, district, appellation and varietal rather than generically. This is now the standard for New World Cabernet Sauvignon wines from Argentina, Australia, California, Chile, New Zealand.|$|R
