5000|$|<b>Ridge</b> <b>Vineyards</b> is a California winery {{specializing in}} premium Cabernet Sauvignon, Zinfandel, and Chardonnay wines. Ridge {{produces}} wine at two winery locations in northern California. The original winery facilities are located at {{an elevation of}} 2300 ft on Monte Bello Ridge in unincorporated Santa Clara County in the Santa Cruz Mountains AVA, south of Los Altos, California and west of Cupertino, California. The other Ridge winery facilities are at Lytton Springs in the Dry Creek Valley AVA of Sonoma County. [...] <b>Ridge</b> <b>Vineyard's</b> 1971 Monte Bello Cabernet Sauvignon achieved international fame for its fifth-place finish in the 1976 [...] "Judgement of Paris" [...] wine tasting.|$|R
